		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_VENETIAN_CA_DORO_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Ca' d'Oro is the Venetian unique building. As Venice cannot annex and thus use a Courthouse, the Ca' d'Oro instead helps to produce [ICON_GREAT_MERCHANT_VENICE] Merchants of Venice, which can be used to purchase or sway city-states. In addition to generating [ICON_GREAT_PEOPLE] GPP, it also has two slots for Merchant Specialists.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_VENETIAN_CA_DORO_TEXT">
			<Text>
				Ca' d'Oro (correctly Palazzo Santa Sofia) is a palace on the Grand Canal in Venice, northern Italy. One of the older palazzi, it has always been known as Ca' d'Oro (golden house) due to the gilt and polychrome external decorations which once adorned its walls.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]An excellent example of the Venetian Gothic architectural style, the Palazzo was built between 1428 and 1430 for the Contarini family, who provided Venice with eight Doges between 1043 and 1676.
			</Text>
		</Row>
